07282nam a22010215i 9780231520119DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20102010nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a2010023732  a(OCoLC)979573645  a97802315201197 a10.7312/guil140802doi  a(DE-B1597)458909  a(OCoLC)750183133  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY00aHQ799.15b.P343 2010 7aPSY0000002bisacsh04a306.87400aParental Monitoring of Adolescents :bCurrent Perspectives for Researchers and Practitioners /ced. by Vincent Guilamo-Ramos, Patricia Dittus, James Jaccard. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2010] 4c©2010  a1 online resource (312 p.) :b8 illus, 12 tables  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tPart I. Contemporary Issues in Parental Monitoring -- t1. Parental Monitoring: A Critical Examination of the Research -- t2. Developmental and Interactional Antecedents of Monitoring in Early Adolescence -- t3. Impediments to Parental Monitoring in the After-School Hours: A Qualitative Analysis -- t4. Cross-Cultural Analysis of Parental Monitoring and Adolescent Problem Behavior: Theoretical Challenges of Model Replication When East Meets West -- t5. When Is Parenting Over? Examining Parental Monitoring and High-risk Alcohol Consumption in Young Adult College Students -- t6. From Research to Practice: Development and Scaling Up of ImPACT, a Parental Monitoring Intervention for African American Parents of Adolescents -- t7. A Three-Process System of Parental Monitoring and Supervision -- tPart II. Expert Perspectives on Parental Monitoring -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe close supervision of adolescents dramatically reduces the incidence of risky sexual behavior, drug and alcohol use, and other activities that could negatively affect one's health and well-being. Because of the strong correlation between parental monitoring and a child's welfare, social workers, psychologists, child development specialists, and other professionals who work with children now incorporate monitoring into their programs and practice. A definitive resource providing the best research and techniques for productive supervision within the home, this volume defines and develops the conceptual, methodological, and practical areas of parental monitoring and monitoring research, locating the right balance of closeness and supervision while also remaining sensitive to ethnic and socioeconomic backgrounds. Assembled by leading experts on childrearing and healthy parent-child communication, Parental Monitoring of Adolescents identifies the conditions that best facilitate parental knowledge, ideal interventions for high-risk youth, and the factors that either help or hinder the monitoring of an adolescent's world. The volume also sets a course for future research, establishing a new framework that evaluates the nature and approach of monitoring within the parent-adolescent relationship and the particular social realities of everyday life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAdolescent psychology. 0aBehavior disorders in adolescencexPrevention. 0aParent and teenager. 0aVigilance (Psychology) 0aVigilance (Psychology). 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh1 aAbar, Caitlin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBelle, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouris, Alida, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDishion, Thomas J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDittus, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab